New York Pride: through the lens of @andrewtess 🌈 

‘The project was something I started right before COVID-19, in 2019. I felt this urge to shoot portraits with people in the community. The people I relate to and connect with often don’t get as much visibility as they should.

As a community, we’re always going to be taking two steps forward, one step back. There’s no such thing as perfection, but we’re building towards a better world. The highlight for me this weekend was the artists, the performers that were there. That for me is Pride.’ - Andrew Tess #SohoHouse @sohohousenewyork

We speak to him about his journey from Zolani in South Africa to Toronto, blending styles of dance, and creating opportunity for Black individuals in spaces that were not historically built for them.

latestPosts.caption:
Soho House Festival 2025

We hosted a very special edition of our annual festival this week, supported by @porsche_gb and @samsung.ads. Members flocked to west London’s Gunnersbury Park, ready for a day of headline music and comedy, plus, of course, unlimited food, drinks, and dancing.

From memorable performances by The Streets, Texas and Craig David, to dance DJ sets by Fat Tony and Groove Armada, and pop-ups from member food favourites Berenjak and Wright Bros – with a pit stop for manicures at the Beauty Tent – here are the highlights from the sun-drenched event.

latestPosts.caption:
‘Off Script With The Hollywood Reporter’ at The Luckman Club⁠
⁠
Located on the first floor of Soho House West Hollywood on the iconic Sunset Boulevard, The Luckman Club is one of the most special events spaces within our Houses. The club takes inspiration from classic Hollywood glamour and features three unique rooms with views over the Los Angeles skyline and Beverly Hills. With this nod to old Hollywood, it’s no surprise it has become home for the filming of The Hollywood Reporter Roundtables.⁠
⁠
Last winter, we hosted some of the movie industry’s biggest names – from actors and actresses to directors and producers – to discuss their projects ahead of awards season. And in recent months, filming has returned to The Luckman Club. In the run-up to 2025’s Emmy Awards, talent from all areas of the TV industry arrived for insightful, funny, and sometimes emotional, discussions about their work.⁠
⁠
To read more, follow the link in bio.⁠
⁠
@hollywoodreporter⁠
@beaugrealy

Interior spotlight: Ludlow House ⁠
⁠
Opened in 2016, the House is set in a 143-year-old former gold leaf factory in the heart of Manhattan’s artistic Lower East Side. ⁠The four-story House has two floors of club space dedicated to dining and lounging, a 26-seat screening room, and regular events programming. ⁠
⁠
Explore the House via the link in bio.

A look inside our Soho House Mexico City bedrooms⁠
⁠
Situated in Colonia Juárez, our Baroque-inspired casa contains four bedrooms inspired by the House’s French heritage with features created by local designers. During your stay, enjoy our largest Soho House pool in the Americas, or head to the tequila bar where everything from mezcal to Margaritas awaits. ⁠
⁠
